{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Momardi","author":"Tuesday Gutierrez"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"0ef97d43-e753-5f2c-9692-8375fdf20bed","excerpt":"Pach just bought me some new  motorcycle boots  as we are now daily commuting to Central London by motobike. Going by bike in the highway is…","html":"<p>Pach just bought me some new <strong>motorcycle boots</strong> as we are now daily commuting to Central London by motobike. Going by bike in the highway is quite scary and I do catch myself from time to time shutting my eyes whenever we squeeze in-between two trucks.  But its a cheap way to travel compared to taking the tube everyday. So for now, I gotta wear the boots.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/momardi/static/a6a16ab7cc0c159e8fdd6f985b8a6b03/bf413/P1020180_qjy03e.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 600px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"P1020180 qjy03e\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/a6a16ab7cc0c159e8fdd6f985b8a6b03/bf413/P1020180_qjy03e.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/a6a16ab7cc0c159e8fdd6f985b8a6b03/b6e67/P1020180_qjy03e.jpg 158w,\n/momardi/static/a6a16ab7cc0c159e8fdd6f985b8a6b03/8099b/P1020180_qjy03e.jpg 315w,\n/momardi/static/a6a16ab7cc0c159e8fdd6f985b8a6b03/bf413/P1020180_qjy03e.jpg 600w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>They are not just bulky, they are also heavy.  And if stillettos can change a woman´s walk, I can attest to the fact that, these motorcycle boots have transformed my already detestable walk to something more grotesque. Pach calls my walk something akin to that of the <strong>grandma Fratteli</strong> in the movie <strong>The Goonies</strong>.</p>\n<p>And if you do remember her, I can say I am also beginning to develop some scowl  in my face as I drag these heavy, bulky, new boots to <strong>****</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.whitecube.com/\" title=\"White Cube\">White Cube Mason´s Yard </a>to see <strong>Mona Hatoum´s exhibit Bunker.</strong></p>\n<p>*<em>**<a href=\"./images/5476190246_e377d80ce3_sc151v.jpg\">\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 500px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"5476190246 e377d80ce3 sc151v\"\n        title=\"5476190246_e377d80ce3\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/4a2d4387e64f099df6a7dc43c96a7ff4/74465/5476190246_e377d80ce3_sc151v.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/4a2d4387e64f099df6a7dc43c96a7ff4/613b8/5476190246_e377d80ce3_sc151v.jpg 158w,\n/momardi/static/4a2d4387e64f099df6a7dc43c96a7ff4/52cfc/5476190246_e377d80ce3_sc151v.jpg 315w,\n/momardi/static/4a2d4387e64f099df6a7dc43c96a7ff4/74465/5476190246_e377d80ce3_sc151v.jpg 500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">5476190246_e377d80ce3</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      </a></em><span style=\"color: #888888;\">Suspended by Mona Hatoum. Photo by</span><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/7984380@N02/5476190246/\" title=\"Mona Hatoum swings\">Michaela Freeman</a>*</p>\n<p>In the ground floor gallery is the installation <strong>Suspended</strong> where 35 red and black wooden swings are chained from the ceiling all placed in an oblique angle.  <strong>Maps were carved into the seats</strong>, each of them being unique. I hardly noticed which cities these maps represent but the whole structure of the installation, even the constricting spaces between the swings also represent a sensation of movement and the act of passing through. Somehow, it was the same sensation I find whenever I go on a motorcycle and swerve for an open space in between cars.</p>\n<p>I went around each swing barely checking the map on the seats and avoided being bumped by the swings in constant motion. That was the experience. Everytime I see artists tackle issues of landscape (connected with identity), I remember a favorite American artist named <a href=\"http://www.arcspace.com/architects/lin/sys_landscapes/sys_landscapes.html\" title=\"Maya Lin´s Systematic Landscapes\"><strong>Maya Lin and her Systematic Landscapes</strong></a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Mona Hatoum</strong> was born into a Palestinian family in <strong>Beirut, Lebanon</strong> and it comes as no surpise that the installation Bunker in lower ground floor suggests the aftermath of a war. Again it looked like an <strong>architecture of a city burnt to the ground by war</strong> with structures made of steel tubes. Each gaping hole just doubled the eerie sensation. It was a ghost town and it was Hatoum´s Beirut.</p>\n<p><a href=\"./images/P1020181_go4dbw.jpg\">\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 500px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 120%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"P1020181 go4dbw\"\n        title=\"P1020181\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/3110c0359b348fd4209467cc4c0281a8/74465/P1020181_go4dbw.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/3110c0359b348fd4209467cc4c0281a8/613b8/P1020181_go4dbw.jpg 158w,\n/momardi/static/3110c0359b348fd4209467cc4c0281a8/52cfc/P1020181_go4dbw.jpg 315w,\n/momardi/static/3110c0359b348fd4209467cc4c0281a8/74465/P1020181_go4dbw.jpg 500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">P1020181</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      </a><span style=\"color: #888888;\"><em>Bunker by Mona Hatoum</em></span></p>\n<p>In the smaller basement, there are three laid out maps of Beirut, Baghdad and Kabul all carefully embellished by cut-out  ections in concentric circles which. Though beautiful,  they all suggest that these were the same locations affected by bomb blasts.</p>\n<p><a href=\"./images/4879787872_85992e125d_k2908x.jpg\">\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 375px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"4879787872 85992e125d k2908x\"\n        title=\"4879787872_85992e125d\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/131ccd7f39d10d73a8a545ae0c915c2e/a2bb6/4879787872_85992e125d_k2908x.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/131ccd7f39d10d73a8a545ae0c915c2e/6b67e/4879787872_85992e125d_k2908x.jpg 158w,\n/momardi/static/131ccd7f39d10d73a8a545ae0c915c2e/14247/4879787872_85992e125d_k2908x.jpg 315w,\n/momardi/static/131ccd7f39d10d73a8a545ae0c915c2e/a2bb6/4879787872_85992e125d_k2908x.jpg 375w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 375px) 100vw, 375px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">4879787872_85992e125d</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      </a><em><span style=\"color: #888888;\">3d-Cities by Mona Hatoum. This photo was taken at another gallery Kunsthall 44 in Germany. Photo by</span><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/birgittesp/4879787872/\" title=\"3d cities\">Birgitte Svaerke Pederson</a></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"youtube\"><div>\n          <div\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\"\n            style=\"padding-bottom: 78.90625%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\"\n          >\n            <iframe allowfullscreen class=\"youtube-player\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/9H_lX1yB0Ho?wmode=transparent&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;iv_load_policy=3&amp;showsearch=0&amp;rel=0&amp;theme=dark\" title=\"YouTube video player\" type=\"text/html\" style=\"\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          \"></iframe>\n          </div>\n          </div></iframe></span><br>\n<em><span style=\"color: #888888;\">Mona Hatoum on her  Suspended installation</span></em></p>\n<p>Mona Hatoum wins the 2011 Joan Mir0 Prize. Read the news <a href=\"http://www.whitecube.com/news/250/\" title=\"Mona Hatoum Joan Miro\">here</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"My Heavy Boots and Mona Hatoum´s Bunker at White Cube","date":"April 06, 2011"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2011-04-06---swinging-by-mona-hatoums-bunker-at-the-white-cube/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/portfolio/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Tuesday's portfolio"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2011-04-06---exit-through-the-gift-shop/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Mr. Brainwash Brainwashes in the Banksy Film: Exit Through the Gift Shop"}}}}